.TH "drm_mode_create_tv_properties" 9 "drm_mode_create_tv_properties" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_mode_create_tv_properties \- create TV specific connector properties
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_mode_create_tv_properties
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_modes "  ","
.BI "const char * const modes[] "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "num_modes" 12
number of different TV formats (modes) supported
.IP "modes" 12
array of pointers to strings containing name of each format
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called by a driver's TV initialization routine, this function creates
the TV specific connector properties for a given device.  Caller is
responsible for allocating a list of format names and passing them to
this routine.
